</a>

<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/node-js-community-member-level-iii">
<img src="https://acclaim-production-app.s3.amazonaws.com/images/1d781431-488d-4052-b477-7609c195723a/Node-js%2BMember%2B-%2BLevel%2BIII.png"
style="vertical-align:middle;width:100%">
</a>
</td>

<td style="vertical-align:top;width:80%;style="color:rgb( 34 , 34 , 34 );font-family:&#39;arial&#39; , &#39;helvetica&#39; , sans-serif;font-size:12px">

<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:16px"><strong><span style="color:rgb( 25 , 112 , 176 );text-decoration:none" target="_blank">
	<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/node-js-community-member-level-i">Node.js Community Member - Level I</a><br>
	<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/node-js-community-member-level-ii">Node.js Community Member - Level II</a><br>
	<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/node-js-community-member-level-iii">Node.js Community Member - Level III</a></span></strong></p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">To become a Node.js Community Member, you must have an established presence in the Node.js community and be committed to learning the technology, taking the initiative to grow professionally, and support your local technology community. Holding this badge demonstrates that you understand the importance of continuous learning, and of independently exploring learning opportunities.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">This badge signifies your involvement in the Node.js community. There are multiple levels of this badge, which are awarded based upon your level of participation in Node.js meetups or conferences over a period of time:</p>
		<ul dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li><strong>Level I: </strong>Awarded for participating in 3 Node.js events in 12 months.</li>
			<li><strong>Level II: </strong>Awarded for participating in 6 Node.js events in 12 months.</li>
			<li><strong>Level III: </strong>Awarded for participating in 12 Node.js events in 12 months.</li>
		</ul>

	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px"><strong>How to earn the badge</strong></p>
		<ol dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li>Attend and participate in the required number of Node.js meetups or conferences within a period of 12 months.</li>
			<li>Send an email to <strong><a href="mailto:treed1&#64;us.ibm.com">treed1&#64;us.ibm.com</a></strong> with the following information:
			<ul>
				<li>Full name of the badge you are requesting</li>
				<li>First and Last name</li>
				<li>Email address</li>
				<li>Details of badge completion, documenting each Node.js meeting or conference you attended by including a link to the event and the event dates.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		</ol>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td style="vertical-align:top;width:20%">
