<td style="vertical-align:top;width:80%;style="color:rgb( 34 , 34 , 34 );font-family:&#39;arial&#39; , &#39;helvetica&#39; , sans-serif;font-size:12px">

	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:16px"><strong><span style="color:rgb( 25 , 112 , 176 );text-decoration:none" target="_blank"><a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/node-js-contributor">Node.js Contributor</a></span></strong></p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">The Node.js Contributor badge signifies a dedication to Node.js technology, as well as an understanding of the Node project, its goals, and the needs of the developer community.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">This badge holder is committed to the success of Node.js through direct contributions to the core Node framework, or to one of the top Node modules on the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">npm website</a>.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">To earn this badge, you must contribute to the core Node project itself, or contribute to one of the top downloaded packages on the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/">npm website</a>.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px"><strong>How to earn the badge</strong></p>
		<ol dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li>Either:
				<ul>
				<li>Make a verifiable contribution to the nodejs/node Github repository (using your Github ID), or</li>
				<li>Contribute to one of these npm <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/browse/star">most-starred modules</a> or these <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/browse/depended">most-depended-upon modules</a>.</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Send an email to <strong><a href="mailto:treed1&#64;us.ibm.com">treed1&#64;us.ibm.com</a></strong> with the following information:
			<ul>
				<li>Full name of the badge you are requesting</li>
				<li>First and Last name</li>
				<li>Email address</li>
				<li>Details of badge completion, documenting your verifiable contribution. Include your Github username, along with the name and link to either the merged commit (for a node core contribution) or npm module.</li>
			</ul>
			</li>
		</ol>
</td>
</tr>

