<td style="vertical-align:top;width:80%;style="color:rgb( 34 , 34 , 34 );font-family:&#39;arial&#39; , &#39;helvetica&#39; , sans-serif;font-size:12px">

	
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:16px"><strong><span style="color:rgb( 25 , 112 , 176 );text-decoration:none" target="_blank">
		<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-advocate-level-i">LoopBack Advocate - Level I</a><br>
		<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-advocate-level-ii">LoopBack Advocate - Level II</a><br>
		<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-advocate-level-iii">LoopBack Advocate - Level III</a></span></strong></p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">To become a LoopBack Advocate, you must demonstrate active knowledge sharing in the LoopBack and Node communities. Holding this badge demonstrates that you have the initiative and skill to create and deliver technical content, and that you have an applied and practical understanding of the technology. Skilled presenters can quickly become a thought leader in the LoopBack and Node space.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">This badge signifies your knowledge-sharing contributions to the LoopBack community. There are multiple levels of this badge, awarded based upon your level of contributions accumulated through LoopBack user groups, conferences, and postings (blogs, articles, podcast, video, and so on):</p>
		<ul dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li><strong>Level I: </strong>Awarded for delivering your first presentation or post.</li>
			<li><strong>Level II: </strong>Awarded for delivering 5 presentations or posts.</li>
			<li><strong>Level III: </strong>Awarded for delivering 10 presentations or posts.</li>
		</ul>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px"><strong>How to earn the badge</strong></p>
		<ol dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li>Deliver the required number verifiable contributions to the LoopBack community by presenting a user group or conference session, or posting original content (through blogs, published articles, videos, or podcasts) to demonstrate your commitment to knowledge sharing on LoopBack and/or Node.js topics. Any combination of talks and posts is permitted.</li>
			<li>Send an email to <strong><a href="mailto:treed1&#64;us.ibm.com">treed1&#64;us.ibm.com</a></strong> with the following information:
			<ul>
				<li>Full name of the badge you are requesting</li>
				<li>First and Last name</li>
				<li>Email address</li>
				<li>Details of badge completion, documenting each contribution by including a link to the talk (on meetup.com or conference website) or post. All posts will be reviewed by a SME for applicability.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		</ol>

</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td style="vertical-align:top;width:20%">
<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-developer-level-i">
<img src="https://acclaim-production-app.s3.amazonaws.com/images/447f8362-7cc3-40f7-aed1-9836310c5c54/Loopback%2BDeveloper%2BLev%2BI.png"
