</a>

<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-developer-level-iii">
<img src="https://acclaim-production-app.s3.amazonaws.com/images/42a5a60d-1e37-4803-b8ba-a447efd07f5a/Loopback%2BDeveloper%2BLev%2BIII.png"
style="vertical-align:middle;width:100%">
</a>
</td>

<td style="vertical-align:top;width:80%;style="color:rgb( 34 , 34 , 34 );font-family:&#39;arial&#39; , &#39;helvetica&#39; , sans-serif;font-size:12px">
		<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:16px"><strong><span style="color:rgb( 25 , 112 , 176 );text-decoration:none" target="_blank">
		<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-developer-level-i">LoopBack Developer - Level I</a><br>
		<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-developer-level-ii">LoopBack Developer - Level II</a><br>
		<a href="https://www.youracclaim.com/org/ibm/badge/loopback-developer-level-iii">LoopBack Developer - Level III</a></span></strong></p>
	
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">The LoopBack Developer badge signifies a dedication to Node.js and LoopBack technology and an advanced understanding of the LoopBack framework.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">To earn the badge, you must demonstrate a commitment to the success of Node.js and LoopBack through <a href="http://loopback.io/">direct contributions to the LoopBack framework</a> (in the form of accepted Pull Request), or by creating related LoopBack plugins, mixins, or components that help progress the framework.</p>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">There are multiple levels of this badge, awarded based upon your contributions to the LoopBack framework:</p>
	<ul dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li><strong>Level I: </strong>Awarded for contributing 1 accepted Pull Request or plugin.</li>
			<li><strong>Level II: </strong>Awarded for contributing 5 accepted Pull Requests or plugins.</li>
			<li><strong>Level III: </strong>Awarded for contributing 10 accepted Pull Requests or plugins.</li>

		</ul>
	<p dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px"><strong>How to earn the badge</strong></p>
		<ol dir="ltr" style="font-size:14px">
			<li>Deliver the required number of either:
			<ul>
				<li>LoopBack Pull Request (must be accepted by the LoopBack review board), or</li>
				<li>External plugins, mixins, or components for LoopBack.</li>
			</ul>
			<li>Send an email to <strong><a href="mailto:treed1&#64;us.ibm.com">treed1&#64;us.ibm.com</a></strong> with the following information:
			<ul>
				<li>Full name of the badge you are requesting</li>
				<li>First and Last name</li>
				<li>Email address</li>
				<li>Details of badge completion, documenting your verifiable contribution. Include a link to either the pull request or the external component project, as appropriate.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		</ol>

</td>
